    <h2>About Widgets</h2>

    <h3>Webpage</h3>

    <p>Often need to access same websites &amp; web apps, such as a task manager, a social media account, a web mail, a messenger, and so on? Use the Webpage widget to have them opened in your workflow tabs.</p>

    <p>Customize &quot;Session Scope&quot; to specify how the session data should be shared between webpage widgets. This is useful when you want to use a web app with multiple accounts.</p>

    <p>&quot;Show Mobile Version&quot; feature will show a compact mobile version of the website/web app, when it's supported. It's useful when you have multiple widgets on a workflow tab and want most of a webpage's useful content to fit a smaller area.</p>

    <h3>Note</h3>

    <p>Note widget is to store quick notes related to a project, such as thoughts, ideas or another important information you need to keep in front of you.</p>

    <h3>File Opener</h3>

    <p>This widget allows to group files and directories by projects and workflows, and open them in an associated application with a single click.</p>

    <h3>To-Do List</h3>

    <p>A widget to quickly organize tasks with a simple to-do list.</p>

    <h3>Commander</h3>

    <p>Commander widget enables you to predefine command-lines you often need to execute, and run them in Terminal with a single click.</p>

    <h3>Link Opener</h3>

    <p>This widget allows to group links related to your projects, and open them in Web Browser with a single click.</p>

